summary: 2002 CHEVY VENTURE VAN WITH TWO FRONT, AND TWO SIDE AIR IMPACT BAGS.  DRIVERS SIDE OF VAN WAS T-BONED ACCROSS THE ENTIRE SIDE OF THE VAN AND THE SIDE IMPACT BAG DID NOT GO OFF.  THE VAN WAS HIT BY A HUGE BRIGADIER DUMP TRUCK  LEAVING FROM A STOP SIGN.  THE VAN WAS TOTALED.  WHY DIDN'T THE AIR BAG GO OFF?  ACCIDENT WAS ON 11/20/02.
